{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBAZw3k8Pxiryo9d8G5gNK","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t<!-- This file is managed by the ai-builder pipeline. Do not hand-edit. -->\n2\t# Task: metrics\n3\t\n4\t## Goal\n5\t\n6\tIn-memory metrics service for recording and listing frontend user interaction events. Serves on port 8081.\n7\t\n8\tHTTP API (verbatim from spec):\n9\tPOST /events — body: {\"type\":\"click-mouse\"|\"submit-form\",\"userId\":\"<string>\",\"payload\":{}} → 201 with event object {\"id\":\"<string>\",\"type\":\"<string>\",\"userId\":\"<string>\",\"payload\":{}};\n10\tGET /events → 200 JSON array of event objects, each with fields: id, type, userId, payload.\n11\t\n12\tData model: Event{id string, type string, userId string, payload map[string]interface{}}.\n13\tStore: thread-safe in-memory slice; IDs are generated UUIDs on POST.\n14\tPackage layout: store.go (EventStore with Add/List), handlers.go (PostEvent, GetEvents), routes.go (returns http.Handler).\n15\tUnit tests must cover store and handler logic; handler tests use net/http/httptest.\n16\t\n17\t## Context\n18\t\n19\t### Level 1 — fbc6d9-0000-build-1\n20\t\n21\t\n22\t## Components\n23\t\n24\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n25\t\n26\t## Design\n27\t\n28\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n29\t\n30\t## Acceptance Criteria\n31\t\n32\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n33\t\n34\t## Test Command\n35\t\n36\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n37\t\n38\t## Suggested Tools\n39\t\n40\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n41\t\n42\t## Notes\n43\t\n44\t_None._\n45\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"369d4d52-0cbc-4b31-bde6-1cc8939c168e","uuid":"74fa6bf8-397b-4974-9863-6a9d1afe9df9","timestamp":"2026-04-05T09:06:18.417Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/target/project/tasks/main/in-progress/fbc6d9-platform/fbc6d9-0000-build-1/fbc6d9-0000-metrics/README.md","content":"<!-- This file is managed by the ai-builder pipeline. Do not hand-edit. -->\n# Task: metrics\n\n## Goal\n\nIn-memory metrics service for recording and listing frontend user interaction events. Serves on port 8081.\n\nHTTP API (verbatim from spec):\nPOST /events — body: {\"type\":\"click-mouse\"|\"submit-form\",\"userId\":\"<string>\",\"payload\":{}} → 201 with event object {\"id\":\"<string>\",\"type\":\"<string>\",\"userId\":\"<string>\",\"payload\":{}};\nGET /events → 200 JSON array of event objects, each with fields: id, type, userId, payload.\n\nData model: Event{id string, type string, userId string, payload map[string]interface{}}.\nStore: thread-safe in-memory slice; IDs are generated UUIDs on POST.\nPackage layout: store.go (EventStore with Add/List), handlers.go (PostEvent, GetEvents), routes.go (returns http.Handler).\nUnit tests must cover store and handler logic; handler tests use net/http/httptest.\n\n## Context\n\n### Level 1 — fbc6d9-0000-build-1\n\n\n## Components\n\n_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n\n## Design\n\n_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n\n## Test Command\n\n_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n\n## Suggested Tools\n\n_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n\n## Notes\n\n_None._\n","numLines":45,"startLine":1,"totalLines":45}}}
